---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="End-of-Line Packing — Formic"
  description="Palletizing, case packing, case erecting, and AMRs — modular end-of-line systems built for mid-market CPG floors."
  ogTitle="End-of-Line Packing"
  ogDescription="Palletizing, case packing, case erecting, AMRs — proven modular designs deployed in weeks."
>
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://formic.co/packing" slot="head" />

<div class="detail-bc">
  <a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span>End-of-Line Packing
</div>

<section class="detail-hero">
  <div class="si">
    <div class="slabel" style="color:var(--orange)">End-of-Line Packing</div>
    <h1>Built for <em>your line</em>.</h1>
    <p class="lede">Standardized, modular palletizing, packing, and pallet-movement systems — proven across CPG floors, deployed in weeks rather than months.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white">
  <div class="db-grid">
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">01 — Complete Solutions</div>
      <h2>The whole end-of-line, <em>one partner</em>.</h2>
      <p>Most CPG operators stitch together case erecting, packing, sealing, palletizing, and pallet movement from four different vendors with four different SLAs. Formic delivers it as one engineered system, supported under one agreement.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Single point of accountability for end-of-line performance</li>
        <li>Cell-level integration eliminates handoff errors between machines</li>
        <li>Unified data layer across every machine in the cell</li>
      </ul>
      <a href="/#cta" class="larr">Scope my line →</a>
    </div>
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/Focus-7603.jpg" alt="Integrated end-of-line cell" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Integrated end-of-line cell</span></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block lgrey">
  <div class="db-grid flip">
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/Haviland_Products_-_Palletizing.gif" alt="Palletizer running at production speed" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Robotic palletizing · 24/7</span></div>
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">02 — Palletizing</div>
      <h2>Stable stacks, <em>every shift</em>.</h2>
      <p>Gantry and robotic palletizers built for sustained throughput. Clean changeovers between SKUs, consistent stack quality, no worker fatigue, no injuries — and more capacity than the manual baseline they replace.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Mixed-SKU palletizing with vision-guided pick and place</li>
        <li>Pallet patterns programmed at deployment, swappable in software</li>
        <li>Up to 1,500 cases/hour sustained throughput on standard configurations</li>
        <li>Compatible with all major slip-sheet and pallet stretch-wrap systems</li>
      </ul>
      <a href="/#cta" class="larr">Get a quote →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white">
  <div class="db-grid">
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">03 — Case Packing</div>
      <h2>Counts that hit, <em>every time</em>.</h2>
      <p>Top-load and side-load case packing across SKUs, formats, and pack patterns. Consistent counts, predictable cycle times, fewer line stops — and clean integration with the upstream filler and downstream sealer.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Top-load and side-load configurations on the same modular base</li>
        <li>Fast SKU changeover (under 10 minutes for most format swaps)</li>
        <li>Vision-guided count verification on every cycle</li>
      </ul>
      <a href="/#cta" class="larr">See it run →</a>
    </div>
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/CasepackerPromoVideo_NoText.gif" alt="Case packer running" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Top-load · Side-load</span></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block lgrey">
  <div class="db-grid flip">
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/Talos-0095.jpg" alt="Case erector and sealer cell" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Erect · Pack · Seal</span></div>
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">04 — Case Erector / Sealer</div>
      <h2>From flat blank to <em>sealed case</em>.</h2>
      <p>Automated case forming and sealing integrated with the upstream packer. One continuous flow, one set of operators, one SLA across the cell — and dramatically lower variability than manual case forming.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Hot-melt or tape sealing options</li>
        <li>Quick blank changeover for SKU mix</li>
        <li>Integrated with case packer and palletizer in one cell</li>
      </ul>
      <a href="/#cta" class="larr">Talk to engineering →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block dgrey">
  <div class="db-grid">
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">05 — AMRs</div>
      <h2>Pallet movement <em>without the forklifts</em>.</h2>
      <p>AMR-driven pallet handling between zones — dock to staging, line to wrap, finished goods to outbound. Running alongside your team, not in place of it, and dramatically reducing forklift-related injuries and product damage.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Fleet sizes from 2 to 30+ AMRs, scalable as you grow</li>
        <li>Dynamic routing — adapts to changing floor layouts</li>
        <li>Integrated with WMS and ERP for real-time inventory tracking</li>
        <li>Safe by design — slows and stops around humans automatically</li>
      </ul>
      <a href="/#cta" class="larr">See AMR fleets →</a>
    </div>
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/Talos-0143.jpg" alt="Autonomous mobile robot moving a pallet" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Autonomous pallet movement</span></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-cta">
  <h2>Run your end-of-line<br><em>without running yourself ragged.</em></h2>
  <div class="btn-row">
    <a href="mailto:sales@formic.co" class="btn-ctadark">Get Started</a>
    <a href="/" class="btn-ctawh">Back to Home</a>
  </div>
</section>
</Layout>
